flowRoot.flowPara: When a photo is selected, the dialog becomes an action dialog with Change and Cancel buttons. Handles allow image crop.
First section includes (in order):
- Images from online accounts
- Previously taken profile pictures
- Previous used profile pictures
- The automatically generated profile picture
- Take a picture (only shown if there's a camera)
The Cancel button returns to the photo selection grid.
Becomes an action dialog when take a picture is pressed. Main view shows a preview from the camera, and an action bar slides up to show a take picture button.
Once a picture has been taken, it is possible to crop before selecting it. The Take Another button returns to the previous step.
Second section includes a selection of stock images to choose from (this should only be shown if setting the image for a user account.
Taking a picture
Action bar slides up from the bottom and camera feed is shown in the main area. Back button cancels taking a picture and returns to the initial state.

After a picture is taken controls for cropping the image are displayed. Take another discards the image and reinstates the camera feed and shoot button. Done closes the dialog, adds the picture to the profile pictures dialog and selects it.
